    </arrangement>
    <bioghist id="aspace_14073797a1362f663b76173f0dd93fd8">
      <head>Historical Note</head>
      <p>Selling Areas-Marketing, Inc. (SAMI) was founded by J. Clarke Mattimore, a consultant in the Time-Life Broadcast division, in 1965 to measure the sale of products by tracking inventory in wholesale warehouses. Reports produced from this information were offered for sale by subscription to consumer-goods manufacturing companies. Time Inc. Sold SAMI in 1987.</p>
      <p>Citations:</p>
      <p>Associated Press. "Time Will Sell SAMI-Burke to Control Data." Los Angeles Times, 14 Oct. 1987, www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1987-10-14-fi-9248-story.html. </p>
      <p>Prendergast, Curtis, and Geoffrey Colvin. 1986. <title render="italic">Time Inc.: The Intimate History of a Changing Enterprise, 1960-1980</title>. New York: Atheneum.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <custodhist id="aspace_006a7a31f9ec8cb2235ca2aea5b79109">
      <head>Provenance</head>
      <p>Gift of Time Inc. in 2015.</p>
    </custodhist>
    <prefercite id="aspace_d97d30201e552db627d57355380c2b1d">
      <head>Preferred Citation</head>
      <p>This record group should be cited as Time Inc. Selling Areas-Marketing, Inc. (SAMI) Records, MS 3009-RG XX, New-York Historical Society.</p>
    </prefercite>
    <processinfo id="aspace_701d924b62c9b7d678d181937b2f8283">
      <head>Processing Information</head>
      <p>The Time Inc. Selling Areas-Marketing, Inc. (SAMI) Records were processed by Allen Thomas in 2020. The original folders were retained although some documents were transferred to archival containers in instances of overcrowding. Allen Thomas created the inventory and other descriptive notes to produce this finding aid.</p>
    </processinfo>
    <relatedmaterial id="aspace_57dbb5841e4e53f40f438f7288b51334">
      <head>Related Materials</head>
      <p>This finding aid relates to just one record group of the Time Inc. Records. For information about the other record groups and for overall information about the archives, please see the Guide to the Time Inc. Records (MS 3009). The Henry Luce Papers (MS 3014) were acquired with the Time Inc. Records. The collection of books acquired with the records are cataloged as the Time Inc. Reference Library.</p>
    </relatedmaterial>
    <scopecontent id="aspace_020d6bc5efa194e40c1f9df50cd97a40">
      <head>Scope and Contents</head>
      <p>The collection consists of reports on product re-stocking at retail warehouses and correspondence with paying subscribers to these reports.</p>
    </scopecontent>
